{
  "texts": [
    "AUROC across the three cross-folds was 0.80, 0.84, and 0.78, with AP of 0.79, 0.83, and 0.77 (Fig. 11).",
    "Dropout-based uncertainty quantification was used for confidence threshold determination.",
    "A final model was then trained across the full dataset using the previously determined optimal hyperparameters and the Tensorflow backend.",
    "When validated on the external test set comprised of 459 slides from TCGA, the model resulted in an AUROC of 0.87 and AP of 0.80.",
    "Using uncertainty quantification and confidence thresholding, 89.5% of slides had high-confidence predictions, with an AUROC of 0.88 within high-confidence predictions."
  ]
}